Version 0.4.0: 2026-07-07
  - New: sort_by (default | distance | rating | popularity), min_rating, and
    radius_miles parameters on HappyCowler and the search_restaurants MCP
    tool. Sorting and filtering run before max_results, so "top N by X"
    queries work. Popularity sort fills the review counts that "Top Rated"
    cards hide from the venue pages before ranking.
  - New: distance_miles, latitude, longitude fields in MCP output; distances
    result column on HappyCowler.
  - Fixed: the map seed is now the median of the city page's nearby-city
    links. The page has no canonical coordinates for the city itself, and
    seeding from the first link (a random suburb) skewed distances and made
    crawl coverage vary between runs.
  - Fixed: WAF challenge pages (HTTP 200 with no microdata) are no longer
    cached as venue details; challenged fetches back off 5s and retry once.

Version 0.3.1: 2026-07-07
  - New: Global politeness throttle — at most one HTTP request per second to
    HappyCow, shared across all threads. Override the interval (or disable
    with 0) via the HAPPYCOW_MIN_REQUEST_INTERVAL environment variable.
    Sustained faster crawling trips the WAF, which then serves challenge
    pages that silently empty the deep-crawl fields.
  - New: Listing cards' own rating and review count are parsed, so ratings
    survive deep_crawl=False and blocked detail fetches. Caveat: "Top Rated"
    venues show a badge instead of a count on their card; their review count
    only exists on the venue detail page (schema.org reviewCount).
  - New: reviews (review count) result column and MCP output field.

Version 0.3.0: 2026-07-03
  - Fixed: Crawler rewritten for HappyCow's current JavaScript-rendered site.
    The old server-side listing markup (div.row.venue-list-item, the "(N)"
    count in the <h1>) is gone; the parser now reads map coordinates from the
    city page, pages through the /ajax/views/searchmap/venues JSON endpoint,
    and reads schema.org microdata from each venue's review page. This fixes
    the misleading "substring not found" error every query used to return.
  - Fixed: Region slugs must use underscores (south_america), not hyphens.
    Docs/examples corrected and 404s now return an explanatory message.
  - Changed: Replaced the defunct incapsula-cracker-py3 dependency with
    curl_cffi, which impersonates a browser TLS fingerprint to get past
    HappyCow's Imperva/Incapsula protection.
  - Changed: Deep-crawl of venue detail pages now runs concurrently and is
    bounded by type_filter/max_results, so only returned venues are fetched.
  - Changed: Unit-test fixtures refreshed to current HappyCow markup.

Version 0.2.4: 2017-08-25
  - New: Functions as a module.
  - New: Unit tests added.
  - Changed: `happycowl` is now the name of the executable.
  - Changed: Updated to latest changes in HappyCow.
  - Fixed: Percentage shown correctly in Python 2.

Version 0.2.3: 2016-09-17

  - New: Progress bar showing current entry processed and a percentage.
  - Fixed: Cities with multiple-page results are crawled correctly.

Version 0.2.2: 2016-08-07

  - Fixed: Python 2 compatibility restored.

Version 0.2.1: 2016-08-06

  - New: Different restaurant types get different colours.
  - Fixed: Single-page results are now correctly parsed.

Version 0.2: 2016-08-06

  - New: It can generate a GPX file for using it with Osmand.
  - New: It works with Python 3.

Version 0.1: 2014-09-12

  - Initial release.
